snippet: Thousands of young men poured into Jordan’s streets for a third night of scattered protests against King Abdullah II, as the United States expressed support for the monarch.
abstract: Thousands of young men take to streets in Jordan for third night of protests against King Abdullah II, as United States expresses support for monarch; protests were set off by anger at reduction in public fuel subsidies.
lead_paragraph: Thousands of young men poured into Jordan’s streets for a third night of scattered protests against King Abdullah II, as the United States expressed support for the monarch.
